    "created_at": "2012-05-24T21:09:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-05-24T21:09:14Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The doc I linked above explains it, but I will reiterate:\n\ncases:\n- ~/.config/ipython exists: IPYTHONDIR = ~/.config/ipython\n- BOTH ~/.ipython AND ~/.config/ipython exist: IPYTHONDIR = ~/.config/ipython\n- ~/.ipython exists AND NOT ~/.config/ipython exists: IPYTHONDIR = ~/.ipython\n- NEITHER ~/.ipython NOR ~/.config/ipython exist (new user/machine):\n  - ~/.config exists: IPYTHONDIR = ~/.config/ipython\n  - else: IPYTHONDIR = ~/.ipython\n\nenvironment variables:\n- If IPYTHONDIR is defined, everything else is ignored.\n- If XDG_CONFIG_HOME is defined, that is used in place of ~/.config.\n\nIt has been discussed a few times that while this does make IPython a better 'platform citizen' on Linux, the occasional confusion may actually be a net detriment.\n"
  },
